description: On one of the BEST blocks in Bernal Heights, 114 Wool is a spectacular modern 3 bed/3 bath home that has just completed a full transformation. 96 Walkscore & steps to the shops & restaurants in Bernal Village. Beautiful to the studs renovation w/the highest quality finishes & gorgeous architectural details with built in cabinetry,box paneled wall & beamed ceilings. New 200 amp electrical, seismic retrofit + foundation upgrades. New roof, windows, floors, plumbing & tankless water heater. Perfect for entertaining, this home has a wonderful open flr plan complete w/a breakfast nook & wet bar that flows effortlessly to the sunny deck. Thermador appliances w/huge 8 ft kitchen island & counters carved from natural marble. Relax in your private full floor master suite completed w/a dressing rm, spa like bath w/soaking tub & duo walk in shower. All finished w/European terrazzo tiles & quartzite stone. Lwr lvl is an excellent space w/2bdrms(1 of which is a master)with direct access to the garden. Laundry, gar parking & stor. Wonderful Bernal location, just above Cortland shops & below Bernal Hill. Easy walk: MUNI, J-Church, tech shuttles, & mins to 101/280.

Fully detached Spanish Mediterranean 4 Bedrooms / 3 Bathrooms, Single Family Home in the prestigious Merced Manor neighborhood! This beautifully maintained home captures all the grand elements of the wonderful homes built in this neighborhood.  The extraordinary home offers soaring vaulted ceilings with intricate detailing across the beams, a custom ornate sky light, two wood burning fireplaces, hardwood floors, and floor to ceiling windows to enjoy your ocean view.        Recently updated with some modern fixtures, while maintaining the home's original character and sophistication.  The home features single garage parking with ample storage and additional driveway space, enclosed backyard patio with mature plants, eat-in kitchen, living room, formal dining room, and family room to make it the perfect future home for any buyer.  The great location of the home starts with its proximity to Stern Grove, Ocean Beach, Stonestown Galleria, Whole Foods and Trader Joes, and is complete with easy freeway and MUNI access.   Simply, this home checks all the boxes and won't last long.  Don't miss this great opportunity.

Enchanting Mediterranean style home on a quiet flat street in prime Forest Hill Extension. Fully detached and flooded with natural light, details include stunning wood beam ceilings, exquisite hardwood floors, staircase with ornate wrought-iron railing, a terra cotta roof, arched doorways and windows and classic hardware and fixtures.     Gracious living room with fireplace and custom window treatments, spacious dining room with arched doorways and recently remodeled light-filled kitchen with quartz countertops, Thermador appliances (including 6 burner gas range), abundant cabinet space and inviting breakfast area with wonderful City outlooks.    The upper level hosts two spacious bedrooms with large closets and a full bath with separate shower and tub.    Lower level offers a large primary suite with sitting area, bathroom with double sinks and 2 walk in closets. There is a large private deck and yard off the primary suite. Additional amenities include a laundry closet with side by side washer and dryer. Well-sized garage with interior access and additional storage underneath the home.  Tranquil location in close proximity to St. Brendan School, the many shops and restaurants of West Portal, Inner Sunset, Forest Hill and West Portal (Muni) Stations and easy freeway access.

Portola semi detached end unit on a hill. 3-bed single family, lots of space to expand, nice outlooks to greenbelt, downtown, The Bay. The kitchen and bath were done in 2009, hardwood floors throughout, large garage, nice backyard.

Welcome to 161 De Soto! As you step inside, you are greeted by a large main level that boasts a well-designed layout. The living room and  dining room plus adjacent chefs kitchen and den flow seamlessly together, creating an open and airy feel. This generous space is ideal for entertaining guests or simply enjoying quality time with your loved ones. The architecture of this home was so well thought out with high ceilings on all levels.   The heart of the home is undoubtedly the chef's kitchen, showcasing exquisite and high-quality finishes. Custom cabinetry provides ample storage, complemented by sleek granite countertops. Quality stainless steel appliances, including a professional-grade gas range, refrigerator, and dishwasher, cater to the culinary enthusiast's every need. A center island with a breakfast bar serves as a focal point, perfect for casual dining or entertaining guests.  Top floor offers 4 BEDs and 3 Baths, including Primary Suite with incredible closet/dressing room. Lower Level has 5th Bedroom and 4th Bath, Social room and wet bar, and more storage than you can dream of! Tons of off street parking, power gate and detached two car garage with More storage! Rear deck and yard is the icing on the cake!

Impeccably maintained, newly renovated Ingleside home complete with panoramic San Francisco views! Situated on a short cul-de-sac, this inviting, move-in ready home is spacious and flooded with an abundance of natural light. The main level of the home features two bedrooms, bathroom, newly remodeled kitchen, dining room, living room and huge sunroom with expansive views. Lower level includes a second bathroom and rooms that can be utilized as additional bedrooms and family room space. The home has been newly painted throughout, and hardwood floors have been newly refinished. Beautifully manicured, low maintenance, paved yard with artificial turf and storage shed, perfect for playing, entertaining and relaxing. Attached one car garage complete with washer, dryer and utility sink. Conveniently located minutes away from BART, MUNI, the 280, Whole Foods, Stonestown Galleria, SFSU, City College and numerous restaurants on Ocean Avenue and Mission Street.

The convenience of the city and the seclusion of the suburbs are both in full bloom at 101 Poppy Lane. This 2008 SFR on an XL lot is totally hidden from passersby.  Social areas take advantage of stunning southwest views and are crowned by large skylights.  Living room includes fireplace, cozy nook, and a view deck. Beautiful luxe kitchen includes 4 burner Wolf range and other SS appliances, marble counters, ample storage incl. floor-to-ceiling pantry closet.  Dining area opens directly to sunny patio that leads to the upper view deck. Also on this level: linen closet and a skylit powder room.  On the middle level, the primary suite features verdant outlooks, walk-in closet, and ensuite bathroom with an extra-long double-sink vanity, luxurious soaking tub, & separate shower.  Two more bedrooms include large closets and share access to a deck with city views.  Also on this level: second full bathroom and spacious family room or office that could easily be used as a fourth bedroom.  Enjoy 3+ car parking and an EV charger in the garage.  New solar panels (owned outright). All this just  mile from the vibrant commercial corridor of Glen Park Village and very near nature and a rec center at Glen Canyon Park, plus BART, Muni, and highway access.

Warm and inviting Marina-style single family home recently remodeled with special touches and emphasis on comfort and detail. Interior floor plan features four spacious bedrooms and Sunroom, two elegantly remodeled baths. Primary suite enjoys spacious built-out walk-in closet, ocean views. Addl top level BR features expansive views of Sutro Tower, Twin Peaks. On main living level, two bedrooms outfitted w/ closet systems enjoy access to additional sunroom that opens to a deck leading to extra large backyard. All bedrooms enjoy ceiling fans for optimal air flow. Eat-in Kitchen w/ counter seating, open to Living Room, boasts stainless KitchenAid appliance suite, pasta filler above range, wine refrigerator, elegant tile backsplash, counters & flooring, capped by chic pendant lighting. Wood flooring throughout is illuminated by custom light fixtures, recessed lighting. Formal Dining Room creates seamless opportunities to entertain. Beautiful wood-burning fireplace bolsters classic built-in details of Living Room. Lwr level: large garage w/ ample storage, laundry area w/ sink, at least 2-car tandem parking, separate entrance from driveway, workshop area, and access to an atrium room, to a double-lot backyard - accounting for approx 4,054sf of lot size (w/play structure)! MOVE-IN READY

Online Biding Platform- First time ever on the market! Sitting at the top of a non through road this peaceful and serene double lot at the base of McLaren Park with no side neighbors is a rare find. Unlimited views of the South Bay and San Bruno Park. The lower level includes a living area, full kitchen, two bedrooms, full bathroom and laundry room. Main level holds the family room with fantastic views, an updated kitchen with quartz countertops and hardwood flooring. Master bedroom has vaulted ceilings and an updated bathroom with jetted tub. Third level has 2 bedrooms and a full a bathroom with hardwood flooring throughout. Step out into the backyard with stamped concrete, Ipe wood railing and extensive terracing retaining walls for 100% usability of the lot. Designed for entertaining with multiple gathering areas, bar and red trumpet shaded pergola. Upper terrace has multiple garden beds, plum, pear, and apple trees with another seating area to take in all the views.

Completely remodeled, detached home designed by Tineke Triggs balances modern-day functionality with an exquisite livable feel. The entry sets the tone as you step onto wide planked oak wooden floors under one of many impressive chandeliers and take in both the custom ceiling in the living room and the dedicated dining room, perfect for hosting dinner parties. The family room and open chef's kitchen combo are flooded with natural light from the glass doors that head down to the West facing oversized yard. You'll enjoy quiet casual meals at the grand island with plenty of room to cook alongside loved ones using Thermador appliances and stunning marble countertops. The bedroom level upstairs offers 4 bedrooms (2 en-suite) plus an additional full bath & washer/dryer. Downstairs (5th bedroom) has a separate kitchenette, full bath, and access to the yard. An ideal setup for entertaining guests or a retreat for visitors! All the bells and whistles with this one - NEM2 smart metering with solar panels, air conditioning, Origin Acoustic speakers, Ring cameras, a large garage, and plenty of storage. Located in the highly desirable Richmond District with easy access to Marin and walkable to countless shops/restaurants, Lake & Clement Streets, Mountain Lake Park, and Presidio trails.

Amazing single owner 3,000 sf home. Property consists of five bedrooms, 2-1/2 baths with a full basement. Main level consists of three bedrooms, 1-1/2 baths with hardwood floors, updated kitchen, formal dining room and sunken living room with fireplace. Top floor features two large bedrooms, one bath and private office. Full basement with expansion potential and private yard.

Welcome to 741 Pacheco Street. This home offers three bedrooms and two bathrooms on the main level. The view from the living and dining area is amazing. Two of the bedrooms lead directly to the backyard deck. The kitchen has been wonderfully updated and has counter eating space. The inside staircase leads to the basement which offers a recreation room. The basement stairs lead to the garage which has two car, side by side parking. A small area beneath the stairs was made into storage for wine. The backyard has a nice sized deck and three additional levels to use for gardening, or a tiered sitting area. The bedrooms are offset from the living area by a small staircase. Main level has a fireplace with insert. 741 Pacheco Street is a wonderful home that can altered to your liking. Centrally located and close to West Portal and the Inner Sunset. Fantastic opportunity.

Welcome to your beautiful move-in ready single family home located in the desirable Outer Parkside neighborhood! This charming home features three - bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a office/gym space, all situated on a generous 2,996 sqft lot.  As you enter, you will be greeted by the bright and spacious living room, perfect for entertaining guests or simply relaxing after a long day. The updated kitchen is a chef's delight, complete with sleek Bosch appliances and ample cabinet space. There are two spacious rooms, and an updated bathroom on this level offering a flexible floorplan and views of the yard.  Head downstairs to find an en-suite bedroom, perfect for guests or as a master suite, offering privacy and comfort. The back of the home includes a bonus office/gym space, providing plenty of room for all your needs.  The backyard is low maintenance and ready for the new owner to make it their special space.   Don't miss this special home that is close to public transportation, parks, restaurants, cafes, AndyTown Coffee Roasters, playgrounds, shopping, HWY 101/280 and much more!

Built in 1912, this beautiful home exudes elegance and is a true gem in one of San Francisco's most desirable neighborhoods. The main level features a spacious living room with fireplace and lovely outlooks. The formal dining room offers period built-ins, intricate moldings, and overlooks the private tiered backyard with deck and patio. Bright updated kitchen with a breakfast bar, Thermador appliances and ample storage. A half bathroom off the kitchen completes this floor. The upper level opens to three generously-sized bedrooms and two bathrooms. The primary bedroom consists of an impressive walk-in closet and bathroom with double vanity and dual shower. The two additional bedrooms have City/Downtown views and are accompanied by a full bathroom with bathtub/shower combination and double vanity. This property also provides a bonus space on the lower level - great for a home gym, office or media area. Hardwood floors throughout, double pane widows, custom window treatments, new carpet on the stairs, one car garage  and abundant storage. Situated on a coveted block, 49 Woodland is just minutes from the many shops & restaurants of Cole Valley, Sutro Reserve, UCSF, and Goldman Tennis Center.

Situated on large corner lot, this fully remodeled Mid Century Modern home has 3 bedrooms, 4 bathrooms and an open concept main living area with Chef-grade kitchen, center island and Thermador appliances (six burner range, refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave and wine storage). Well proportioned bedrooms, motorized shades, and one comes with a Murphy Bed, allowing it to double as an office. The primary bedroom boasts 2 bathrooms with design-grade fixtures, shower, soaking tub, Toto Washlet toilets, floating vanities, and heated towel warmer. There are two large closets, with custom built cabinetry. A separate ADU doubles as a family room with full kitchen, that leads directly out to a professionally landscaped, fenced, low maintenance back yard with drip irrigation. A wood deck area for dining and lounging, and a hot tub make for great indoor/ outdoor living. An over-sized garage has room for two cars and storage.Modern updates include: tankless hot water heater, recessed lighting, full size W/D, triple paned windows, smart home technology, keyless entry system, security cameras, central heat and AC (main level). Buyers will appreciate this rare, well designed home with overlooks of Glen Canyon, a short distance to Noe Valley and the Castro, and easy access to the freeways.

Welcome to 682 Duncan...This stunning remodeled home positioned in the heart of Noe Valley features 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, and an alluring blend of contemporary design, comfort, and functionality.    The main living space is outfitted with an updated kitchen that seamlessly connects to the dining and living spaces with direct access to the view deck creating a compelling indoor/outdoor living experience.To complete this level are two bedrooms and a bright, full-size bathroom with walk-in shower and separate soaking tub. The primary bedroom suite resides on the lower level and features a luxurious en-suite bathroom with walk-in shower, heated floors and ample closet space. A spacious laundry with sink and storage completes this level.    The level outdoor space lends itself to entertainment, play and family gatherings.  Additional features include hardwood floors throughout, designer tile, 1-car parking & additional storage. Convenient location minutes away from 24th St. corridor, Glen Park Canyon, Douglass Playground and Church St. restaurant & businesses. Don't miss this turnkey opportunity in one of the most desirable neighborhoods of San Francisco!

Rare opportunity to own a home in the highly sought-after Inner Sunset neighborhood with the potential to customize renovations to your liking.  Natural light streams through the windows in the main level of this home which features a living room, a separate dining room, two bedrooms, sunroom and a split bathroom.    Downstairs includes high ceilings, offering unlimited possibilities for expansion. The backyard includes a spacious yard for you to transform into various options such as a beautiful garden, a play area for children, or an area for outdoor gatherings.  Conveniently located to Sunset area schools, transportation, shopping and popular restaurants.

Breathtaking fully remodeled property located in the scenic city of San Francisco!  This exquisite residence boasts views of the iconic Golden Gate Bridge & the majestic Sutro Tower, providing an unparalleled backdrop for luxurious living. As you step into this remarkable home, you will notice the meticulous attention to detail. The kitchen features marble counters & is equipped with top-of-the-line appliances. The white oak floors lend an air of sophistication, while designer finishes add a touch of modern elegance. With a total of 5 bedrooms & 4.5 bathrooms, this property offers ample space for both relaxation & entertainment. The high ceilings create an airy & spacious ambiance, while deck spaces on every level allow for seamless indoor-outdoor living. The beautifully maintained outdoor space offers a sanctuary for relaxation & entertainment, complete with lush greenery & a charming atmosphere. This property is a true masterpiece in one of San Francisco's most desirable locations.

Incredible Location and first time on the market in 50 years! This gorgeous, split level 2 bed, 1 bath, 1,360 square foot home is located in the hugely desirable Lakeside neighborhood.  Pride of ownership together with tasteful updates, make this 1939 construction seem modern and new. Beautifully refinished hardwood floors on the main level shine with all the natural light this home allows in.  Fresh paint throughout and brand new carpet both upstairs, as well as in the bonus room down.  Bonus room down features an updated full bath, access to both garage and backyard, in addition to separate entrance capabilities.  Newer kitchen complete with breakfast area, which leads to the simple, but nicely landscaped backyard.  Formal dining room adjacent to breakfast area allows for an easy flow to the home, as well as, making it great for entertaining. 1 car garage with additional off-street spot in the driveway, plus ample street parking, Ocean and 19th Avenues less than a block away, steps to MUNI access, walk to Stonestown, SF State and West Portal.  Easy access to any and all conveniences make this a true gem in San Francisco.

Prepare to be wowed! Extraordinarily large (4554) lot with amazing City and Bay views affords an unmatched indoor-outdoor lifestyle, complete with stunning roof deck, charming home office at back of the lot, firepit, fountain, and luscious blooms. Many recent improvements by current owners include roof deck, office structure, new electrical service, dual Tesla chargers, Tesla solar panels, Powerwall backup battery, mud room, laundry room with plenty of storage and home gym. The home is set in a peaceful cul-de-sac overlooking Douglass Park and is an easy walk to the amenities of 24th Street. This open, airy home is suffused with light and offers an open floor plan and 3 BR/2BA on one level with no steps necessary to access the sunny south facing garden; true indoor-outdoor living. This ideal floor plan is complemented by a fourth ensuite bedroom or office on the lower level and two car side by side parking with two Tesla chargers and two more in the deep driveway. The home was extensively remodeled in 2019 by the previous owners for themselves and uses timeless, top-of-the-line finishes and appliances. This home has incredible style but is also very functional for daily living--sexy and practical.

Open house Saturday July 5th, 12PM - 4PM!

Two story house, 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths plus multiple bonus rooms! New kitchen, updated bathrooms, hardwood floor, fresh paint. In-unit washer/dryer is included. Everything brand new! One block from Golden Gate park and Ocean beach. Couple steps away from Judah St & La Playa St Muni. One car garage + drive way parking. Shares backyard with the ADU in the back. Not furnished. Lower level (1 bed, 1 bath, bonus rooms) has own entrance.

Small dog or cat is welcome. Income must be at least 2x rent. $6000 deposit. Tenants pays electricity/gas and water. Trash pickup is included in rent. $35/adult application fee.

Showing by appointment after work hours or any time over weekends. Please text/email with your name, phone number, number of occupants and monthly income to arrange showing.

100 Judah is a grand & stately home with over 4,000 square feet of interior space that graces the corner of Judah & 6th Ave in the prime Inner Sunset. Filled w/ history, it has remained in the same family for over 60 yrs. The classic Edwardian architecture provides both timeless elegance + an ideal floor plan. Although it is definitely a fixer'', it doesn't require an expansion/major floor plan changes for it to be the epic landmark home of your dreams. The foyer divides the main floor w/ a spacious living rm on the right & dining rm on the left. Both rooms feature fireplaces & built-ins. A large kitchen & laundry room run parallel to the dining rm, while a sunroom leads to a staircase to the garden. The 2nd floor has 3 bedrms & 1 full bath, while the 3rd floor has 2 bedrms, a 2nd full bath + an extra room. The bedrms are generous in size & filled w/ light. The baths need updating but provide an opportunity for customization. A staircase from the main level leads to a full basement offering potential for playrm, fitness, storage, etc. A separate garage provides parking/storage. This large Edwardian home in a phenomenal neighborhood boasts square footage + a terrific floor plan. It requires a fair amount of TLC but its natural beauty & undeniable potential justify the investment.

Updated Outer Sunset home conveniently located just half block from Noriega Street restaurants & shops, both Noriega St & 46th Ave public transit, Ocean Beach, & West Sunset Playground. Top floor features living room, dining area, updated kitchen with breakfast area, two bedrooms, and bath. Ground floor offers additional room added in 1964 (On record in 3R, but with no additional info on status) and one large car parking with additional space for storage. Partial ocean views from the top floor! Upgrades include kitchen and bath remodel several years ago, new luxury vinyl floor over existing hardwood floor on the top floor, new luxury vinyl floor on ground floor room, and new interior & exterior paint! Huge flat yard!

Bursting with authentic SF charm, this 3 bdrm Parkside gem is the perfect place to call home. The center of the home, accessible via French Doors from the kitchen, is a sun-filled, usable center patio providing cozy outdoor space for morning coffee and an area to entertain guests. Gleaming hardwood floors greet you upon arrival & flow continuously through the voluminous living room w/fireplace, formal dining room & to 2 generously sized bedrooms & beautifully remodeled bathroom. The remodeled Chef's kitchen is equipped with top of the line Bosch appliances, ample counter space & tons of storage. The lower level features an extensive primary bedroom with a large walk-in closet, renovated full bathroom, direct access to the low-maintenance sunny backyard & enormous 2 car garage with extra storage space & laundry. Walkable to numerous parks including Pine Lake Park & Stern Grove, Ocean Beach, countless neighborhood restaurants & easy access to Muni all contribute to this A+ location.

Stunning, fully detached house with the desirable layout of 3 bedrooms on one level on a coveted block in West Portal - a cherished San Francisco neighborhood. This updated home not only has a great layout and sought-after location it also has an impressive kitchen, gorgeous natural light and curb appeal. The main level features a welcoming entryway, large living room with a gas fireplace, formal dining room and chef's kitchen with a nice-sized breakfast nook. Only a few steps up to the upper level are its 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. The primary bedroom is spacious and comfortable. The lower level offers a big bonus space that can be wonderful for entertaining, working from home and working out. The sizable garage has interior access and a lot of storage space. There is 2 car parking in the garage and 1 car parking in the driveway. Beautiful hardwood floors and period details enhance the character of the home. Freshly painted interior and exterior. Low maintenance front yard and backyard complete this property. Near the heart of West Portal Village and its numerous popular restaurants, cafes and shops. Conveniently located by Muni, Stonestown, Stern Grove and schools. Short drive to the freeway, Lake Merced, Fort Funston and Ocean Beach. This special house checks off the boxes.

Welcome to 458 Mangels Avenue, a charming Edwardian, nestled on a tranquil street in the Sunnyside Neighborhood! The home is detached on three and a half sides and has a bright interior that includes a spacious kitchen, and formal dining room, two bedrooms, a Jack-and-Jill bathroom and a comfortable living room. There are large doors from the kitchen that lead to a deck and patio area in the serene garden---making it a wonderful indoor/outdoor home. It has a basement with ample storage space and garage for one vehicle, as well as a driveway space for another vehicle.   Features of note include: original period details, hardwood floors, a box-beam ceiling in the dining room, dual-paned windows, a claw foot tub, a bonus sleeping loft in the rear bedroom, original built-in bookshelves and China cabinet, 10 foot ceilings, tasteful lighting fixtures, a landscaped front and rear garden, located adjacent to Sunnyside park and playground, the home is also close to transportation, dining and shopping on Monterey Blvd. Ocean Ave. and Glen Park Village.

Welcome to this charming and spacious single-family home on wide, easy-to-drive-through Holyoke Street! 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom on the main level with a large living room plus fireplace, a formal dining room, a kitchen with breakfast nook and plenty of cabinets. Lower level has 2 bedrooms, a permitted bathroom and a galley kitchen - easily functional as two separate units. The house has hardwood floors throughout, a skylight in the hallway, and a one-car garage with washer/dryer. The backyard is perfect for entertaining and sipping your favorite cabernet under the gazebo, accessible from both levels. City approvals to build a backyard deck ready in hand too. Conveniently located near San Bruno Avenue row of shops, restaurants, John McLaren Park, schools, and public transportation. Close to Silver Avenue, 101 and 280 for easy access to downtown San Francisco and the Peninsula. Don't miss this opportunity to own this lovely home in a desirable neighborhood!

This California Bungalow captures views of urban hillsides, San Bruno Mt and coastal landscapes.  Enter from the semi glass-enclosed front porch into the foyer-living areas with built-ins and gas fireplace.  An abundance of light fills these rooms through eight windows spanning the full width of the property.  A full bath with a cast iron bathtub and primary bedroom lie off a hallway from the foyer.  An adjacent doorway in the living area leads to an open kitchen-dining room with access to a bedroom with half bath and the upper deck and laundry room.  With coastal views and westerly sunsets, the lower deck leads down to the lush gardens and sitting area.  Situated on an expansive flat lot perched a few feet above the sidewalk, street and park, the Bungalow faces east and has a front yard lined by a picket fence.  On the other side of the yard, a path follows along the side of the house through a wooden gate to the backyard and decks.  The entranceways to the detached garage and the lower level with two bonus rooms and a full bath are along this pathway.  This property appeals to both those seeking move-in ready or a visionary's canvas, all with its original character of a classic 1916 SF Bungalow intact.

666 3rd Avenue is a thoughtfully-designed three bedroom + den, two bathroom home with exceptional natural light and floor-plan. The main level features a light-filled foyer, spacious living room, formal dining room, kitchen with new countertops, bathroom with walk in shower, home office/den and direct access to the large terrace and garden perfect for outdoor dining and entertaining. The upper-level features three bright bedrooms with ample closet space and one bathroom. The lower level offers great expansion potential with a two-car tandem garage, laundry room and storage area. 666 3rd Avenue is located a block and a half from the best of Golden Gate Park, Conservatory of Flowers, Lisa & Douglass Goldman Tennis Center, steps to Rossi Park and Pool, and just around the corner from some of the local favorite cafes and restaurants including the Arguello Market, Velo Rouge Cafe, and the Cinderella Bakery & Cafe on Balboa Street.

Charming tunnel entrance home on a prime Outer Sunset block. Both bedrooms on the main level are spacious and overlook the inviting backyard. An ornate fireplace gives the living room a nice refined feel. Natural light floods the kitchen and dining room. Off the hall is a large tiled bathroom with a separate shower & tub. Downstairs features a handy third bedroom and second bathroom. The garage offers abundant space for parking, storage, and laundry. 1518 40th is ideally situated just a few blocks away from Ocean Beach, Golden Gate Park, and all the conveniences of Judah. Don't miss it!

Great location near Noriega, Ocean Beach, Park Merced, Golden Gate Park, SF Zoo. Move in ready, well maintained home, beautiful hardwood floors, updated windows, updated lighting, fireplace, numerous skylights offers plenty of natural light. Sliding glass door from guest bedroom to large rear deck, with stairs and ramp to lower yard. Washer/Dryer on lower level with laundry chute from upper bathroom. 
Rear patio partially covered by deck, tool shed, greenhouse, terraced yard three levels. 
Section 1 pest clearance, newer furnace. Enjoy the Big City lifestyle in a neighborhood that feels like the suburbs. Open Houses to make previewing the property easier. Come take a look in person, its even better than the photos.

Charming updated home in the heart of the Parkside neighborhood. Light filled, gleaming hardwood floors, bay window, updated throughout. Functional floorpan offering multi-gen living potential with a separate living space that includes a kitchen, full bathroom and bedroom. Attached sunroom that creates the perfect flex space for office, yoga, studio etc. Well appointed main kitchen features a 5-burner gas range, dishwasher, built-in microwave and fridge. Private, landscaped backyard complete with a deck, garden boxes and low maintenance turf. Spacious garage and driveway. Walkable location close to Golden Gate Park, Ocean Beach, SF Zoo, dining, brewery, coffee shops, public transportation & shopping. Don't miss this wonderful home!

This "Belle of the Sunset" gives old school, Frank Sinatra, San Francisco vibes with its grand staircase, chandeliers, glass doorknobs, formal dining room, and other classic nooks and crannies. It's been thoroughly cleaned, freshly painted, wood floors refinished! Owned by the same family for over 60 years, the home has been well maintained! Bedrooms are large, house is spacious and clean, garage area has lots of storage, and backyard is a blank slate for gardeners!

Welcome to this pristine and impeccably maintained four-bedroom and three-bathroom residence. This outstanding property is nestled on the premiere cul-de-sac block in the coveted Forest Knolls neighborhood. The main level offers a perfect floor plan featuring sun-drenched living and dining rooms, lovely refinished parquet hardwood floors, wood burning fireplace, period built-ins, a bright eat-in kitchen, three large bedrooms and two full baths. Off the main hall, the wide interior stairway leads you to the lower level boasting an additional expansive bedroom ( or media room ) and full bath overlooking the lush landscaped and serene garden. This floor is completed by a large two-car side by side garage, laundry area and ample room for expansion. Forest Knolls is centrally located in the City's geographic center and offers a unique lifestyle among the peaceful forest and lovely greenbelt, Midtown Terrace Playground, Sutro Reserve with both walking and bicycle paths plus underground utilities. Close to UCSF, Cole Valley, 9th@Irving and West Portal Village offers both excellent public and private schools and transportation within just one block.Don't miss this home. It has been impeccably maintained and you will see and feel the difference!

Nestled in the Castro neighborhood, this 4-bedroom, 2-bathroom home sprawls 2,248 square  feet with a fantastic backyard and exceptional curb appeal. Built in 1905 the interiors showcase a  convergence of timeless original charm with modern upgrades. Natural light pours into the  living room, which features a gas fireplace, hardwood floors, and charming pocket doors that  lead to the dining room with a built-in bar, stained glass accents, and French doors to the back  deck. The beautifully upgraded kitchen is outfitted with high-end   Viking stainless steel appliances including a wine fridge, a Sub-Zero refrigerator, Calacatta marble countertops,  Waterworks finishes, and ample storage. Upstairs, retreat to privacy with 3 spacious bedrooms  with plenty of closet space and a gorgeous bathroom with marble accents, dual sinks, and an  expansive walk-in shower. The home's lower level offers a full bathroom, laundry, storage, a 1-  car garage, and a bedroom with backyard access that could also be a media or recreation room. Relax in your private backyard sanctuary with magnificent trees, landscaping, green space, and a patio with a fire pit. With a 99 Walk Score enjoy restaurants, bars, shopping, groceries, public transportation, and parks in moments.

Its hard to pick one thing to love about this home. Is the weather the best thing? According to the Golden Gate Weather Service this house is in the warmest, sunniest patch of SF. Right around Garfield Square. Glorious kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, lots of counter space. The kitchen is completely open to the living/dining area with a bay window. Beautiful floors. This house is all about lifestyle. Entertaining and family living.  On this floor there is a bedroom being used as an office right now and a full bathroom which is gorgeous. The second floor has a huge primary suite w/ bath. Lovely full hall bath, the third bedroom and large nook under eaves with a window that overlooks the amazing backyard full of fruit trees.
